WEBVTT

00:14.600 --> 00:15.800
CHAPTER XIV

00:17.180 --> 00:23.120
And I looked, and lo, a lamb stood on the Mount Sion, and with him an hundred forty

00:23.120 --> 00:27.580
and four thousand having his father's name written in their foreheads.

00:27.580 --> 00:33.060
And I heard a voice from heaven as the voice of many waters, and as the voice of a great thunder,

00:33.320 --> 00:38.100
and I heard the voice of harpers harping with their harps. And they sung, as it were,

00:38.340 --> 00:44.220
a new song before the throne, and before the four beasts, and the elders. And no man could learn

00:44.220 --> 00:48.760
that song but the hundred and forty and four thousand which were redeemed from the earth.

00:49.440 --> 00:54.600
These are they which were not defiled with women, for they are virgins. These are they

00:54.600 --> 00:59.760
which follow the Lamb whithersoever he goeth. These were redeemed from among men,

00:59.900 --> 01:05.960
being the firstfruits unto God and to the Lamb. And in their mouth was found no guile,

01:06.120 --> 01:12.120
for they are without fault before the throne of God. And I saw another angel fly in the midst of

01:12.120 --> 01:17.180
heaven, having the everlasting gospel to preach unto them that dwell on the earth, and to every

01:17.180 --> 01:22.100
nation, and kindred, and tongue, and people, saying with a loud voice,

01:22.800 --> 01:29.980
Fair God, and give glory to him, for the hour of his judgment is come, and worship him that made

01:29.980 --> 01:36.680
heaven, and earth, and the sea, and the fountains of waters. And there followed another angel,

01:37.020 --> 01:44.420
saying, Babylon is fallen, is fallen, that great city, because she made all nations drink of the

01:44.420 --> 01:50.820
wrath of her fornication. And the third angel followed them, saying with a loud voice,

01:51.360 --> 01:57.720
If any man worship the beast and his image, and receive his mark in his forehead or in his hand,

01:58.040 --> 02:02.560
the same shall drink of the wine of the wrath of God which is poured out without mixture

02:02.560 --> 02:09.000
into the cup of his indignation. And he shall be tormented with fire and brimstone in the presence

02:09.000 --> 02:15.120
of the holy angels and in the presence of the lamb. And the smoke of their torment ascendeth

02:15.120 --> 02:21.480
up for ever and ever. And they have no rest day nor night who worship the beast and his image,

02:21.680 --> 02:27.980
and whosoever receiveth the mark of his name. Here is the patience of the saints. Here are

02:27.980 --> 02:33.700
they that keep the commandments of God and the faith of Jesus. And I heard a voice from heaven

02:33.700 --> 02:39.900
saying unto me, Right, blessed are the dead which die in the Lord from henceforth.

02:40.440 --> 02:46.140
Yea, saith the Spirit, that they may rest from their labours, and their works do follow them.

02:47.020 --> 02:54.180
And I looked, and behold a white cloud, and upon the cloud one sat like unto the Son of Man,

02:54.380 --> 03:01.100
having on his head a golden crown, and in his hand a sharp sickle. And another angel came out

03:01.100 --> 03:08.340
the temple, crying with a loud voice to him that sat on the cloud, Thrust in thy sickle and reap,

03:08.660 --> 03:15.020
for the time is come for thee to reap, for the harvest of the earth is ripe. And he that sat

03:15.020 --> 03:21.200
on the cloud thrust in his sickle on the earth, and the earth was reaped. And another angel came

03:21.200 --> 03:26.880
out of the temple which is in heaven, he also having a sharp sickle. And another angel came

03:26.880 --> 03:32.360
out from the altar which had power over fire, and cried with a loud cry to him that had the

03:32.360 --> 03:39.540
sharp sickle, saying, Thrust in thy sharp sickle, and gather the clusters of the vine of the earth,

03:39.800 --> 03:46.300
for her grapes are fully ripe. And the angel thrust in his sickle into the earth, and gathered the

03:46.300 --> 03:52.420
vine of the earth, and cast it into the great winepress of the wrath of God. And the winepress was

03:52.420 --> 03:56.200
trodden without the city, and blood came out of the winepress,

03:56.420 --> 04:02.500
even unto the horse-bridles, by the space of a thousand and six hundred fur-lawns.

04:04.000 --> 04:05.800
The end of chapter 14.

